The paper describes the use of machine learning algorithms and convolutional neural networks for analyzing ECG data to detect and track diseases. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the development of a novel model for ECG segmentation, which could fall under the category of computer engineering (cs.CE). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of ECG data for medical decision-making, which could fall under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC) or neuroscience and emerging technologies (cs.NE).
